	(text "Congratulations!\nYou have successfully pulled the KiCad files from the GitHub repository! Yippee!\nThe next step is to make a change to the schematic and/or the layout and push the changes to a new branch of the repository.\n\nStep-by-Step Instructions:\n1. Change the schematic/layout and save the file after changing it\n2. Go into the layout editor (The Git plugin interface can only be accessed through the layout editor for reasons)\n3. Launch the Git plugin interface\n4. Set your User Name and Email under Edit->Options so that the plugin knows who you are and will let you commit\n5. Create a new branch and name it first_initial-last_name\n6. Make sure all of your changes are unstaged by clicking Rescan\n7. Click Stage Changed to prepare your changes for a Commit\n8. Write in the Commit Message what you changed\n9. Click Sign-Off for formalities\n10. Click Commit\n11. Click Push to push the changes to the branch you just created\n\nThis is the project workflow of using Git with KiCad!\nAll that is left to do is to go back into GitHub and create a Pull Request if you are done making changes on your branch and it is ready to be merged with the main"
